# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat     A new feature
#   fix      A bug fix
#   docs     Documentation changes
#   style    Formatting-only changes (no logic)
#   refactor Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     Performance improvement
#   test     Adding or fixing tests
#   chore    Build/CI/tooling or other maintenance
#
# Scope:
#   Optional. Use a short area name (e.g., queue, cmake, ci, docs, benchmarks).
#
# Subject:
#   - Imperative mood ("add", "fix", "update")
#   - Keep it concise (aim for <= 50 chars)
#   - No trailing period
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at ~72 chars per line
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues/PRs (e.g., "Closes #123")
#   - Mark breaking changes with "BREAKING CHANGE:"
#
# Example:
#   feat(queue): add backoff strategy
#
#   Explain motivation and high-level approach.
#
#   BREAKING CHANGE: rename try_pop to pop_try
#   Closes #123
